Sho Madjozi attends BET International Cocktail Voyage at Hotel Figueroa on June 22, 2019 in Los Angeles, California. JOHANNESBURG - Sho Madjozi and Shekhinah have bagged a nomination for the upcoming Nickelodeon Kids' Choice Award. The local stars have been nominated in the Favourite African Star category along with Nigerian singer Teni and Kenyan singer Patricia Kihoro. READ: Sho Madjozi set to perform during Super Bowl weekend Sho Madjozi has also been nominated in the Favourite Global Music Star category. The annual awards show will be held on March 22, 2020, at The Forum in Inglewood, California and will be hosted by Grammy-award winning rapper Chance The Rapper.